title.narrative: **Do Not Use**Digital Access - Technical assistance and capacity building on policy, legal and regulatory frameworks for digital inclusion, through service contracts

description.narrative: This activity (**Do Not Use**Digital Access - Technical assistance and capacity building on policy, legal and regulatory frameworks for digital inclusion, through service contracts) is a component of Digital Access Programme reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £1,909,675. This component benefits Developing countries, unspecified, and works in the following sector(s): Telecommunications, Information and communication technology (ICT), Business Policy and Administration, Small and medium-sized enterprises (SME) development. , with the following implementing partners: Ernst & Young, IMC Worldwide, Oxford Policy Management. The start date is 03-12-2019 and the end date is 31-03-2023.
